Class PreGame

java.lang.Object
commandLineApp.PreGame
public class PreGame

  • Constructor Details

    • PreGame

      public PreGame​(GameManager gameManager)
      This method creates a PreGame. It creates and initalises the Farm, Farmer, Land, Inventory and GeneralStore and gets the pregame user info.
      Parameters:
      gameManager - The central game controller.

  • Method Details

    • runPreGame

      public void runPreGame()
      This method runs the PreGame. A Farmer, GeneralStore and Inventory are created. The FarmAnimalArray, FarmCropArray, FarmAnimalLand, FarmCropLand are initialised. The GameRules are displayed.

    • initializeInventory

      public void initializeInventory()
      This method creates and adds a GrowthFertiliser, ProfitFertiliser, Tractor, AnimalTreat, AnimalFeed and Shovel to the inventoryItemsArray.

    • initializeAnimalArray

      public void initializeAnimalArray()
      This method creates and adds a Chicken, Sheep, Cow to the farmAnimalsArray.

    • initializeCropArray

      public void initializeCropArray()
      This method creates and adds an Apple tree, Blueberry bush, Cherry tree, Grape vine, Orange tree and Strawberry bush to the farmCropsArray.

    • initializeAnimalLand

      public void initializeAnimalLand()

    • initializeCropLand

      public void initializeCropLand()

    • greetUser

      public void greetUser()
      This methods greets the user.

    • askGameDuration

      public void askGameDuration()
      This method asks the user for how long they would like to play the farm simulator game for. It ensures the input is an int between 5 and 10 inclusive. It sets the valid input as the gameDuration.

    • askFarmerName

      public void askFarmerName()
      This method asks the user for their farmer name. It ensures the input is String containing only letters between 3 and 15 in length or/and spaces or/and apostrophes. It sets the Farmer's name from input.

    • askFarmerAge

      public void askFarmerAge()
      This method asks the user for their farmer age. It ensures the input is a positive int. It sets the Farmer's age from input.

    • askFarmName

      public void askFarmName()
      This method asks the user for their farm age. It ensures the input is a String containing only letters between 3 and 15 in length or/and spaces or/and apostrophes. It sets the Farm name from input.

    • printfarmTypeInfo

      public void printfarmTypeInfo()
      This method displays the four Farm types' perk information.

    • askFarmType

      public void askFarmType()
      This method asks the user for their chosen Farm type. It ensures the input is an int between 1 and 4 inclusive. It sets the Farm type from input.

    • createFarm

      public void createFarm()
      This method creates a Farm based on the chosen type of Farm.
